title: "Anxiety in transition: Neuroendocrine mechanisms supporting the development of anxiety pathology in adolescence and young adulthood"
collection: publications
category: manuscripts
excerpt: 'This paper proposes a dual-mechanism model to explain the development of anxiety pathology during adolescence, focusing on pubertal testosterone's influence on orbitofrontal cortex-amygdala circuitry and the myelination of the uncinate fasciculus.'
